text: Henry Purcell (1659–1695) was an English composer. Purcell may also refer to: == Places == *Purcell, Indiana, an unincorporated community in Johnson Township, Knox County, Indiana *Purcell, Missouri, a city in Jasper County, Missouri, United States *Purcell, Oklahoma, a city in and the county seat of McClain County, Oklahoma, United States *Purcell School, a specialist music school in Hertfordshire, England *Purcell Mountains, a component of the Columbia Mountains, British Columbia, Canada ==People with the surname== *Purcell (surname) == Other uses == * Purcell (architects), formerly Purcell Miller Tritton, a British architectural firm founded in 1947
title: Purcell (disambiguation)
